               <head>Commentary on Rumi's Masnavi, first 18 couplets</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010115018 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002005579 http://lccn.loc.gov/n81058129" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16559-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>A commentary in verse, 
                <title>Mas̲navī-'i ‘Abd al-Raḥmān</title>, on the first eighteen couplets of the 
                <title>Mas̲navī</title>of 
                <persName key="viaf_98930150" role="ant">Jalāl al-Dīn Rūmī</persName>. By 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656317.0x000001 viaf_1142152636165320052521" role="aut">‘Abd al-Raḥmān al-mufavviż bi-Llāh ibn al-Shaykh Aḥmad ibn al-Shaykh Maḥmūd al-Qādirī al-Ṭālibānī
                al-Kirkukī</persName>(of Kirkuk). This work is very rare. In the preface (f. 1v-3r), which is in prose, the author praises Shaykh ‘Abd al-Qādir al-Jīlānī and states that in spring
                1250/1834-5, while discussing the Masnavī, he was asked to compose such a work.
                        </p>
                        <p>The title is given in the above form by Munzavī in FNKhF III, p. 3129, where only one other manuscript is recorded: in the Majlis Library, Tehran; but on p. 3414 of the same work,
                in the index of incipits, it is called 
                <title>Mas̲navī-i Ṭāliqānī</title>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Preface begins (f. 1v): Basmala al-Ḥamd li-Llāh allazī aliha ‘uqūl al-fuḥūl fī idrāk Jalālih va qudsih Va l-ṣalāt va l-salām... Bihtarīn saday (sic) kih bulbul-i zabān-i ‘ārifan az
                sar-i shawq va ishtiyāq dar gulshan-i bayān āghāz kunand...</p>
                        <p>Commentary on Masnavī, bayts 1-2 begins (f. 5v): ‘Ishq dar nay chūn navā-rā sāz kard * az zabān-i nay sukhan āghāz kard</p>
                        <p>Ends: Bī riyā khwānad hamīsha īn du‘ā * Istajib yā Dhā l-Ghinā’i va l-‘aṭā</p>
                        <p>Other contents: front endpaper, one bayt of verse in Arabic and one in Persian; back flyleaf, addition sums, etc., with the date 1266/1849-50.</p>
                        <p>Dated 1260/1844-5. Copied by 
                <persName key="person_f7002" role="scr">‘Abd Allāh al-Khiżrī</persName>, possibly at Kirkuk.
                        </p>
                        <p>Clear, non-calligraphic nasta‘līq; Arabic phrases in vocalised naskhī. 13 lines in 2 columns. Text (i.e. lines from the Masnavī) and quotations and headings in red. Text frames:
                gold, black, red. Illuminated heading, of an unusual and provincial-looking form, in a combination of gilt, bright orange, bright green and grey, f. 1v. 13 folios, plus 2 blank. 214 x
                134 mm.; text area 160 x 88 mm. Yellow boards with pink edging and deep red leather spine.</p>
                        <p>Purchased from Christie's South Kensington (11 April 2008, lot 146).</p>
                     </note>
